The paper proposes a deep learning framework for Radon inversion, which is a problem in image reconstruction. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of neural networks for the framework, which suggests machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and training of the neural network, which suggests neural networks (cs.NE) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of clinical patient data, which suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as a possible category.
